## 5. global Block

```yaml
global:
  storageClass: longhorn
  timezone: Asia/Aden
  hostname: <app>.yourdomain.com
  clusterIssuer: letsencrypt-prod
  ingressClassName: nginx
  imagePullSecrets: []    # e.g. [{ name: registry-secret }]
```

---

## 6. Namespace Setup

```bash
kubectl create namespace <app> --dry-run=client -o yaml | kubectl apply -f -

kubectl label namespace <app> \
  pod-security.kubernetes.io/audit=restricted \
  pod-security.kubernetes.io/warn=restricted --overwrite
```

### ResourceQuota (per namespace)

```yaml
apiVersion: v1
kind: ResourceQuota
metadata:
  name: <app>-quota
  namespace: <app>
spec:
  hard:
    requests.cpu: "4"
    requests.memory: 8Gi
    limits.cpu: "8"
    limits.memory: 16Gi
    pods: "50"
    persistentvolumeclaims: "20"
    services: "20"
```

Adjust limits per application. Every pod **must** have `resources.requests` or scheduling fails under quota.

---

## 7. Ingress & TLS

```yaml
ingress:
  enabled: true
  className: nginx
  annotations:
    cert-manager.io/cluster-issuer: letsencrypt-prod
    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/ssl-redirect: "true"
  hosts:
    - host: <app>.yourdomain.com
      paths:
        - path: /
          pathType: Prefix
  tls:
    - hosts:
        - <app>.yourdomain.com
      secretName: <app>-tls
```

**Pre-requisites:** DNS A record → HAProxy IP, port 80 open through HAProxy.

---

## 8. Network Policies (Always — 3 policies)

### 8.1 default-deny-ingress

```yaml
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: default-deny-ingress
spec:
  podSelector: {}
  policyTypes:
    - Ingress
```

### 8.2 allow-internal

```yaml
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-internal
spec:
  podSelector: {}
  policyTypes:
    - Ingress
  ingress:
    - from:
        - namespaceSelector:
            matchLabels:
              kubernetes.io/metadata.name: <app-namespace>
```

### 8.3 allow-ingress (from RKE2 ingress controller)

```yaml
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-ingress
spec:
  podSelector: {}
  policyTypes:
    - Ingress
  ingress:
    - from:
        - namespaceSelector:
            matchLabels:
              kubernetes.io/metadata.name: kube-system
```

> **CRITICAL:** Allow `kube-system` on **ALL ports** — not just app port.
> cert-manager ACME HTTP-01 solver uses random ports (~8089).
> Restricting to port 5678 (or similar) breaks TLS certificate issuance.

