## 13. Images

| Type | Source |
|------|--------|
| PostgreSQL | `postgres:<semver>-alpine` — pin exact version |
| Redis | `redis:<semver>-alpine` — pin exact version |
| App images | Private registry or official upstream |
| Official charts | OCI/subchart from vendor |

- **Pin semver tags** — never `:latest` or `:stable` in production
- **No Bitnami** — use official images with custom templates

---

## 14. Deployment Patterns

### Pattern A — Single umbrella chart

One Helm release, all services, toggled via `*.enabled` flags.

```yaml
postgresql:
  enabled: true
redis:
  enabled: true
app:
  enabled: true
```

### Pattern B — Multiple releases

Release 1: data layer (PostgreSQL, Redis, NetworkPolicy).
Release 2: application (official vendor chart + values overlay).

**Rule:** Install DB/cache **before** application. Wait for pods Ready.

---

## 15. HPA & PDB

```yaml
# HPA — stateless Deployments only (requires metrics-server)
autoscaling:
  enabled: true
  minReplicas: 2
  maxReplicas: 10
  targetCPUUtilizationPercentage: 70

# PDB — ONLY when replicas ≥ 2
pdb:
  enabled: true
  minAvailable: 1
```

- No HPA on StatefulSet DB
- No PDB when `replicas: 1` (invalid)

---

## 16. ServiceAccount & RBAC

```yaml
serviceAccount:
  create: true

rbac:
  create: false    # true only when app needs K8s API
  rules: []        # namespace-scoped Role, least privilege
```

- Dedicated ServiceAccount per chart
- No `cluster-admin`, no wildcard verbs

---

## 17. Standard Labels

```yaml
labels:
  app.kubernetes.io/name: {{ .Chart.Name }}
  app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}
  app.kubernetes.io/version: {{ .Chart.AppVersion | quote }}
  app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: {{ .Release.Service }}
  app.kubernetes.io/component: api   # api | worker | db | cache
```

