## 18. Pre-Deploy Checklist

```bash
kubectl get nodes                                          # Ready
kubectl get ingressclass                                   # nginx (default)
kubectl get clusterissuer letsencrypt-prod                 # Ready
kubectl get storageclass longhorn                          # (default)
kubectl get pods -n longhorn-system                        # Running
kubectl get pods -n cert-manager                           # Running
kubectl get pods -n kube-system -l app.kubernetes.io/name=rke2-ingress-nginx  # Running
nslookup <hostname>                                        # → HAProxy IP
helm lint . -f values.yaml -f values-ci.yaml
helm template <release> . -n <ns> -f values.yaml -f values-ci.yaml
```

---

## 19. Post-Deploy Validation

```bash
kubectl get pods,svc,ingress,pvc,certificate -n <namespace>
curl -I https://<hostname>/health
helm get values <release> -n <namespace> > backup-values.yaml
```

---

## 20. Upgrade & Rollback

```bash
# Snapshot etcd before cluster-level changes (on master node)
rke2 etcd-snapshot save --name pre-<app>-upgrade-$(date +%Y%m%d)

helm upgrade --install <release> ./helm/<chart> \
  -n <namespace> \
  -f values.yaml \
  -f values-production.yaml \
  --atomic --wait --timeout 10m

helm history <release> -n <namespace>
helm rollback <release> <revision> -n <namespace>
```

---

## 21. Cursor Agent Rules

1. **This file is the only source** — no external docs required
2. **Platform is deployed** — adapt the app, never redesign infrastructure
3. **Never assume** undocumented values — ask the user
4. **Every chart must include:** Deployment/StatefulSet, Service, NetworkPolicy (×3), probes, resources, securityContext
5. **No cloud features** — on-prem Contabo VPS + HAProxy, no LoadBalancer
6. **Pin image tags** — semver only
7. **Schedule on worker** — avoid control-plane node for app workloads
8. **Install order:** namespace → secrets → data layer → app layer → verify TLS

